2-Ingredient Everything Bagel Chicken Wings
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'wings (wingettes or drumettes)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'everything bagel seasoning'}
steps: Preheat an air fryer to 390 degrees F (199 degrees C).. Place wings in a large bowl. Sprinkle everything seasoning over the top. Using your hands, mix well until wings are evenly coated.. Place wings in the basket of the air fryer, skin side up. Cook for 20 minutes. Shake and cook until crisp, about 3 minutes more.

name: Cranberry Brie Pull Apart Bread
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 (', 'unit': '1 1/2 to 1 3/4', 'name': 'sourdough loaf or crusty Italian bread, unsliced'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'fresh rosemary'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'fresh thyme'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '8-ounce', 'name': 'rie cheese, cut lengthwise in 1-inch strips, then thinly sliced crosswise'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dried cranberries'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with foil. Cut bread with a serrated knife from the top nearly to the bottom in diagonal 1-inch diamonds (do not cut through).. Combine melted butter, honey, rosemary, thyme, pepper, and salt in a small bowl.. Gently pull bread open at cuts and evenly drizzle with half of the butter mixture.. Stuff Brie and cranberries into the cuts as you go.. Place loaf on prepared baking sheet and drizzle with remaining butter mixture.. Bake until the Brie is melted and the bread is toasty, 20 to 25 minutes. Serve immediately.

name: Honey Glazed Halloumi
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(7 ounce) block', 'name': 'halloumi cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'minced garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'sesame seeds'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili pepper flakes,'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': 'fresh', 'name': 'fresh'}
steps: Slice halloumi lengthwise into 6 equal slices and pat dry with a paper towel. Add halloumi slices to a shallow container.. For glaze, combine honey, sesame oil, lime juice, minced garlic, sesame seeds, and chili flakes in a small bowl. Spoon glaze over halloumi, cover, and marinate in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour or up to overnight.. Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat. Place halloumi in the pan, leaving plenty of space between slices. Cook until slices are a nice golden brown, 1 to 2 minutes per side. They will brown quickly.. Lower the heat to a simmer, add any remaining glaze to the skillet to quickly warm up. Spoon glaze over halloumi until well coated.. Place halloumi slices on a plate with some fresh lime wedges, drizzle with any leftover glaze in the skillet, and serve immediately.

name: Ginger-Orange Upside-Down Tarts
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'oranges'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fig jam'}, {'quantity': '5 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crystallized ginger'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'fresh rosemary, plus more for garnish'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'rie cheese,'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'sheet', 'name': 'frozen puff pastry dough'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg, lightly beaten'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Line a large baking sheet with parchment paper.. Cut peel and white pith from oranges, then cut crosswise into 1/2-inch-thick slices. Stir together jam, honey, ginger, and rosemary in a small bowl.. Spread 2 tablespoons jam mixture into 6 small (approximately 2x3-inch) rectangles (1 teaspoon jam mixture each) on the parchment, spacing them about 2 inches apart. Reserve remaining jam mixture for topping.. Arrange 1 or 2 orange slices and 1 Brie slice over each rectangle.. Cut puff pastry dough into 6 equal rectangles. Prick dough all over with a fork. Arrange 1 rectangle over each filling stack, stretching gently as needed to cover. Press edges into parchment to seal in filling. Brush pastry dough with egg.. Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes. (Cover loosely with foil for the last 10 minutes of baking, if needed, to prevent overbrowning.) Let cool for 5 minutes, then turn each tart over using a spatula.. Thin reserved jam mixture with water to reach a drizzling consistency; spoon over tarts and garnish with additional rosemary.

name: Olive Cheese Balls
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sharp Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'flour'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '36', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'pimiento-stuffed green olives'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'ranch dressing for serving'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': 'cracked black', 'name': 'cracked black'}
steps: Combine cheese and butter in a food processor and process until mixed together. Add flour, paprika, and cayenne. Process just until dough comes together. Turn out dough and shape into a disc. Chill, covered, until slightly firm and easy to handle, about 30 minutes.. Meanwhile, drain liquid from olives and spread out on paper towels to dry.(The olives should be completely dry before wrapping with dough.). Line a 10x15-inch rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper. Pinch off a piece of dough about the size of a walnut half. Flatten and wrap around an olive, enclosing completely. Roll to make a smooth ball. Place on the prepared baking sheet. Repeat with remaining dough and olives, spacing olive balls about 1 1/2 inches apart. Freeze until firm, at least 1 hour (and up to 1 month).. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Bake frozen cheese balls until lightly browned and dough is set, 15 to 18 minutes. Let cool 5 minutes. Serve with ranch and garnish with pepper.

name: Best Smoked Salmon Dip
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'smoked salmon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8-ounce)', 'name': 'cream cheese, softened'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green onion, finely chopped, plus more for garnish'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'capers, drained'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'fresh dill, plus more for garnish'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt-free Creole seasoning'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'crackers and crostini, for serving'}
steps: Flake smoked salmon with a fork.. Beat together cream cheese and mayonnaise in a large bowl with an electric mixer at medium speed until smooth. Add red onion, green onion, capers, lemon juice, dill, and Creole seasoning; mix well. Gently fold in smoked salmon.. Chill in an airtight container at least 2 hours (and up to 3 days). Garnish with additional dill and green onions. Serve with crackers and crostini.

name: Smoked Turkey Collard Green Dip
ingredients: {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'cream cheese,'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'collard greens'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'smoked turkey'}, {'quantity': '2 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded cheese blend - C'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'hot sauce'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'fresh parsley'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Coat a 2-quart baking dish with cooking spray.. Beat cream cheese and sour cream together in a large bowl with an electric mixer on medium speed until smooth. Fold in collard greens, turkey, 1 1/2 cups cheese, and hot sauce. Transfer to the prepared baking dish and top with remaining 1 cup cheese.. Bake in the preheated oven until cheese is melted and golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes. Garnish with smoked paprika and parsley.

name: Creamy Jalapeno Cranberry Dip
ingredients: {'quantity': '2/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dried cranberries'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'jalapeno pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pickled jalapenos'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red onion'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(8 ounce) packages', 'name': 'cream cheese'}, {'quantity': '2/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'asiago cheese'}
steps: Place cranberries in a small bowl and cover with boiling water. Let stand for 3 minutes to soften slightly and drain.. Add cranberries, jalapeno, pickled jalapeno, brine, red onion, and sugar into a food processor and pulse until very finely chopped.. Combine cranberry mixture with softened cream cheese and asiago cheese and stir until well blended. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

name: Beet Pickled Deviled Eggs
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'beets'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'apple cider vinegar, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'peppercorns'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'hard boiled eggs'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'Dijon mustard'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'apple cider vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'dash', 'name': 'hot sauce'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'radish slices'}
steps: For brine, drain beet juice into a small saucepan; set beet slices aside. Add the 1/2 cup vinegar, sugar, salt, and peppercorns, and bring to a low boil over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves, 3 to 5 minutes. Let cool completely, about 20 minutes.. Place eggs in a jar or glass bowl just large enough that brine will completely cover eggs; pour in brine. Top up with vinegar as needed to cover eggs completely. Refrigerate, covered, for at least 12 and up to 24 hours. The longer eggs are in brine, the deeper pink they will be.. Slice eggs in half lengthwise from top to bottom with a sharp knife. Remove yolks and place in a bowl. Mash yolks with a fork until smooth, and stir in mayonnaise, Dijon, the 1 teaspoon vinegar, and hot sauce; season with salt and pepper. As an option, if you have a small food processor, place all filling ingredients in it, and blend until smooth.. Spoon filling evenly into egg whites or add mixture to a piping bag or resealable plastic bag with one corner clipped. Pipe mixture into egg white halves, garnish as desired, and serve.

name: Cranberry Cheese Ball
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cranberry juice cocktail'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dried cranberries, snipped, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8-ounce) package', 'name': 'cream cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chives, divided'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'orange zest'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pecans, toasted and finely chopped'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'crackers, crostini, and/or vegetable dippers for serving'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Bring cranberry juice just to a boil in a small saucepan. Remove from heat. Add 1/4 cup dried cranberries. Cover; set aside.. Place cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, and butter in a large bowl. Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.. Drain cranberries, reserving 1 tablespoon juice. Add plumped cranberries and reserved juice to the bowl with the cheese mixture. Add 1 tablespoon chives, orange zest, brown sugar, and garlic powder. Beat with an electric mixer on medium until light and fluffy.. Place cheese mixture on a sheet of plastic wrap. Use the plastic wrap to shape the mixture into a ball (it won’t be a perfect shape at this point). Wrap in the plastic wrap and chill in the refrigerator for 3 to 24 hours.. Now you can make a better ball shape by rolling the wrapped mixture on your work surface.. Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup dried cranberries, remaining 1 tablespoon chives, and the pecans on a sheet of plastic wrap or waxed paper. Roll cheese ball in the mixture to coat.. Let stand 15 minutes before serving with crackers, crostini, or vegetable dippers.

name: Coconut Chicken Tenders
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'boneless chicken breast tenderloins or skinless, boneless chicken breasts, cut into 1-inch thick strips'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt, divided'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'riracha'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'panko bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsweetened shredded coconut'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'sesame seeds'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sweet chili sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'riracha'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C). Place a wire rack in a 18x13-inch rimmed baking sheet. Coat rack with nonstick cooking spray. Sprinkle chicken tenders with 1/2 teaspoon salt, set aside.. Place flour in a small shallow dish. Whisk together egg and Sriracha in a second shallow dish. Combine panko, shredded coconut, sesame seeds, paprika, garlic powder, and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt in a third shallow dish. Drizzle panko mixture with olive oil and mix until coated evenly.. One at a time, dip chicken  tenders into the flour, shaking off the excess, then dip into the egg mixture to coat. Dredge in the panko mixture, coating all sides and pressing as needed to help it adhere. Place on the prepared rack. Repeat with remaining chicken tenders.. Bake in the preheated oven until chicken is cooked through (165 degrees F or 74 degrees C) internal temperature) and golden brown, about 15 minutes.. In a small bowl mix together mayonnaise, Asian sweet chili sauce, and Sriracha.. Serve chicken tenders hot with dipping sauce and enjoy!

name: Truffle Deviled Eggs
ingredients: {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'hard-boiled eggs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Dijon mustard'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'truffle oil'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': '', 'name': 'truffle salt'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chives'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'pieces', 'name': 'truffles (optional)'}
steps: Halve eggs lengthwise and scoop egg yolks into the bowl of a mini food processor; set egg whites aside. If you do not have a mini food processor, you can mash all ingredients in a bowl with a fork.. Add mayonnaise, Dijon mustard, truffle oil, salt, and pepper to the egg yolks; blend well until smooth, scraping down the sides of the bowl. If mixture is too thick, blend in an extra teaspoon or two of mayonnaise.. Place yolk mixture into a resealable bag and snip off a corner. Pipe mixture into egg whites. Top with chives and shaved truffle, and refrigerate until ready to serve.

name: Chicken Adobo Tacos
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white vinegar'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'bay leaves'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'granulated garlic'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'skinless, boneless chicken thighs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'white vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'fish sauce'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'avocado oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'white pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'mango'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'oma tomato'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red onion'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'jalapeno pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'garlic cloves'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper,'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '(8 inch)', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'chopped cilantro'}
steps: Combine soy sauce, vinegar, bay leaves, and garlic in a large plastic bag with a zipper. Gently squeeze to mix well. Add chicken and coat with marinade. Squeeze out as much air from the bag as possible, coat all the chicken pieces with marinade, seal, and refrigerate for at least 20 minutes.. Meanwhile, combine vinegar, fish sauce, avocado oil, sugar, and black pepper in a bowl for the salsa. Stir with a whisk or fork until sugar is dissolved. Add mango, tomato, red onion, jalapeño, and chopped cilantro to the bowl. Toss to combine, and refrigerate salsa until ready to serve.. For tacos, remove chicken pieces from the marinade and reserve the marinade.. Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Carefully add the chicken thighs, and brown on each side, 1 to 2 minutes, then remove chicken to a plate.. To the same skillet, add onion, and cook for about 1 minute. Stir in minced garlic and cook until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Add reserved marinade, water, brown sugar, and black pepper, and bring to a boil.. Return chicken to the skillet, smooth side down. Reduce heat to low, and simmer chicken uncovered, about 15 minutes. The liquid should bubble gently. Turn chicken and simmer 10 minutes more. Remove chicken from skillet to rest.. Cook sauce over medium heat until syrupy, thick, and reduced, about 10 minutes. Remove skillet from heat. Remove bay leaves and discard.. Slice chicken into 1/2-inch slices and return to the skillet to coat in the sauce. Garnish with fresh cilantro and chopped green onions, if desired.. Fill each tortilla with chicken strips and top with mango salsa. Serve immediately.

name: Roscoe's Chilaquiles
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'chile peppers'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'chile pepper,'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': None, 'name': 'Roma tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'white onion'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'garlic cloves,'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'beef bouillon cube'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'culantro leaves'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'lime, juiced'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '2 1/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'oil, divided'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': None, 'name': 'corn tortillas'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Mexican crema'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'otija cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'avocado,'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cilantro leaves'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'lime'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'oregano,'}
steps: For salsa roja, pour boiling water over peppers and let sit until softened, 15 to 30 minutes.. Meanwhile, add 2 tablespoons olive oil to a skillet over high heat, and sear tomatoes, onions, and garlic until charred for about 2 minutes.. Place softened peppers, charred vegetables, and 1 cup of the chile soaking water in a blender. Reserve remaining 3 cups chile water.  Blend until smooth. Strain the sauce; pour back into the pan.. Cook sauce over medium heat, scraping any charred bits from the bottom of the pan; add 2 cups of remaining chile water. Simmer until sauce is reduced by 1/3. Stir in bouillon cube and last 1 cup chile water, culantro leaves, lime juice; stir until bouillon cube dissolves. Season with salt and pepper.. For chilaquiles, heat oil to 350 degrees F ( 175 degrees C) in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add tortillas and fry until crisp and golden. 2 minutes per batch.. For each serving, heat 1 tablespoon oil in a small nonstick pan over medium heat. Crack an egg into the skillet, and cook until outer edges become opaque, about 1 minute. Turn egg over and cook until whites are completely opaque, 1 to 2 minutes more.. Add a handful of chips to the salsa roja, and turn to coat completely. Remove to a serving plate with a slotted spoon.. Drizzle with crema, top with an egg, cotija cheese, avocado, cilantro, squeeze of lime juice, and drizzle with more salsa roja. Sprinkle with oregano. Repeat with remaining ingredients.

name: Pecan Pie Cheese Ball
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'packages', 'name': 'caramel dip singles'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'toasted pecans'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(8 ounce) packages', 'name': 'cream cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'powdered sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'light brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'package', 'name': 'instant vanilla pudding mix'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'fresh lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': '2/3 cup', 'name': 'pecans, divided'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'apple slices'}

name: Fall Jarcuterie
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'extra virgin olive oil'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'apple cider vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon whole-grain', 'name': 'mustard'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon freshly ground', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'garlic clove, grated'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'ranny Smith apple, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'oneycrisp apple, chopped'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'sharp Cheddar cheese, cubed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'salami, cut into half moons'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cornichons'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'shallot'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dried cranberries'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'walnut halves'}
steps: Whisk together oil, vinegar, whole grain mustard, honey pepper, salt, and grated garlic in a bowl until well combined.. In a large bowl, mix together apples, Cheddar cheese, salami, cornichons, shallots, cranberries, and walnuts until evenly combined. Drizzle with prepared dressing until well coated. Transfer mixture to a large jar with a lid. Shake and store in the refrigerator for up to 5 days or until ready to serve.

name: Beef and Bean Tiny Tacos
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'packet', 'name': 'taco seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '48', 'unit': None, 'name': 'corn tortilla chips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14 ounce) can', 'name': 'refried beans'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'Mexican blend cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped cilantro'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': '1/4'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook while crumbling with a spatula and stirring occasionally until browned, about 5 minutes. Add taco seasoning and water and stir, using a wooden spoon to scrape up any browned bits from the bottom. Cook, stirring occasionally, until meat is well coated in seasoning. Remove from heat and set aside.. Arrange whole chips on the bottom of 2 rimmed baking sheets. Spread each chip evenly with a thin layer of refried beans. Top evenly with taco meat and cheese.. Bake in the preheated oven until cheese is melted, 5 to 7 minutes.. As soon as chips are baked, carefully fold each chip in half to form a taco shape. Place tacos on a serving platter with taco sauce for dipping.

name: Pigs In A Blanket Wreath
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(8 ounce) cans', 'name': 'refrigerated crescent roll dough'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'Dijon mustard'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 ounce) package', 'name': "mini sausages, such as Lil'\xa0Smokies®"}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'everything bagel seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'ground mustard'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'apple cider vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pepper'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'rosemary sprigs for garnish (optional)'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment.. Unroll and separate crescent dough into 16 triangles.  Spread each triangle evenly with Dijon mustard. Use a pizza cutter or knife to make 2 cuts into each triangle to make 3 smaller triangles.. Place 1 piece of cheese and 1 sausage at the bottom of each smaller triangle and roll all the way up. Place about 20 wrapped sausages on the baking sheet in a large circular shape with the sausages radiating from the center, and sides of each roll touching each other. Arrange remaining rolled sausages inside the larger ring, slightly overlapping, to form a double layer ring.. Brush rolls lightly with egg and sprinkle evenly with bagel seasoning.. Bake in the preheated oven until golden brown, 22 to 24 minutes.. Meanwhile, for dipping sauce, combine mayonnaise, honey, stone ground mustard, vinegar, salt, and pepper in a small bowl and and whisk until well incorporated. Pour sauce into a bowl small enough to fit into the center of the crescent ring.. Transfer ring to a serving platter and place sauce bowl inside the ring. Garnish with rosemary stems to resemble a holiday wreath. Serve warm or room temperature.

steps: Whisk together olive oil, wine, 2 tablespoons lemon juice, lemon zest, 1/2 of the garlic, crushed red pepper, oregano, 1 teaspoon salt, and 1/2 teaspoon pepper in a bowl. Add chicken and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes to 1 hour.. Stir together remaining salt and pepper with bread crumbs, panko, Parmesan cheese, and garlic powder in a shallow dish. Remove chicken from marinade and toss to coat in breadcrumb mixture, pressing to adhere as necessary. Thread chicken onto skewers and coat with olive oil cooking spray.. Preheat an air fryer to 390 degrees F (198 degrees C).  Air fry until chicken is no longer pink at the center and juices run clear, and is until lightly golden brown and crisp, about 12 minutes. An instant read thermometer, inserted near the center, should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).. Meanwhile, melt butter with remaining garlic in a microwave-safe dish on High in the microwave, about 10 seconds.  Stir in remaining lemon juice and parsley. Drizzle butter mixture over chicken just before serving.

Meanwhile, for sauce, whisk together yogurt, lemon juice, vinegar, and remaining 1/4 teaspoon pepper in a small bowl. Serve bread, smoked mackerel, beets, and apple with sauce. name: Salted Pretzel Church Window Cookies
ingredients: {'quantity': None, 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'mixed nuts'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'semisweet chocolate chips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dark chocolate chips'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'marshmallows'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'pretzels, crushed'}
steps: Coarsely chop 1 1/2 cups nuts. Finely chop remaining 3/4 cup nuts.. Melt butter in a double boiler or a heat-safe bowl set over simmering water, stirring occasionally. Add semisweet and dark chocolate chips. Heat, stirring constantly, until melted. Remove from heat; let cool 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Meanwhile, put 2 (15x18-inch) pieces of parchment paper on a work surface.. Add marshmallows and coarsely chopped nuts to chocolate mixture; stir gently to coat. Spoon half of chocolate mixture onto center of each piece of parchment paper. Using the parchment or a silicone spatula, shape each portion into a 12-inch-long log. Wrap logs tightly in parchment; chill until surface of chocolate is slightly firm and pulls away from parchment (center will still be soft), 15 to 20 minutes.. Meanwhile, combine finely chopped nuts and pretzels in a small bowl. Put 2 more 15x18-inch pieces of parchment paper on work surface. Sprinkle each with half of pretzel mixture.. Carefully transfer chilled logs (they will still be soft) to the parchment with pretzel mixture; roll, gently pressing to coat all sides. Wrap logs tightly in parchment paper; chill until firm, at least 4 hours or up to overnight.. Cut each log into 1/2-inch-thick slices, trimming off uneven ends as needed. (To store, layer between sheets of waxed paper in an airtight container and chill up to 3 weeks.)

name: Peanut Butter Bugle Bites
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(7 1/2 ounce) bag', 'name': 'crunchy corn snacks (such as Bugles®)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '2/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'light corn syrup'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chocolate chips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'coconut oil'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'sea salt (optional)'}

Combine sugar, butter, peanut butter, and corn syrup in a small saucepan over medium heat. Bring mixture to a boil, stirring often. Boil for 2 minutes, remove from heat, and pour over Bugles. Toss quickly to coat and spread into an even layer.. Combine chocolate chips and coconut oil in a small bowl. Melt in the microwave in 30 second increments, stirring in between each. Drizzle melted chocolate over bugles and let cool completely. For best results, refrigerate for 5 minutes to allow chocolate to harden. Break into large pieces; store in an airtight container.

name: Pumpkin Cheese Ball
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(8-ounce) packages cream', 'name': 'cheese, softened'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'hot pepper sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'minced garlic'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'heddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'bell pepper'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'crackers for serving'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Combine cream cheese, hot pepper sauce, paprika, and garlic in a food processor. Process until well combined.. Add 1 1/2 cups shredded cheese and process until cheese is finely chopped but still very visible.. Sprinkle about 3 tablespoons of the remaining shredded cheese into a 4-inch pile on a large piece of plastic wrap, and top with a rounded scoop of the cheese ball mixture.. Sprinkle the cheese ball mound with the remaining shredded cheese.. Pull sides of plastic wrap up and over the cheese ball mixture to wrap tightly and shape into a ball. (If needed, wrap with an additional piece of plastic wrap to ensure the mixture is very tightly wrapped.). Wrap 4 wide rubber bands around the cheese ball, evenly spacing them to create the indentations that are found on a pumpkin. (Depending on the size of the rubber bands, you may need to double wrap each one to create indentations that are deep enough.). Chill cheese ball in the refrigerator at least 3 hours before serving to allow flavors to meld and the cream cheese to become firm.. Before serving, remove rubber bands and unwrap cheese ball. Place a bell pepper stem on top of the pumpkin and gently press to adhere. Serve with crackers.

Place mixture in a small serving bowl.. Stir honey, peanuts, green onions, and pepper in a small bowl. Pour over cheese mixture and stir to combine.

name: Stuffed Mushroom Dip

name: Chicken Liver Pate
ingredients: {'quantity': '16', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'chicken livers'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shallots'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'clove garlic'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'dried thyme leaves'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'dry sherry'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}
steps: Trim chicken livers of any membrane, dry on paper towels, and set aside.. Melt 4 tablespoons butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the shallots and garlic, and saute until softened, about 3 minutes.. Add chicken livers, thyme, sherry, salt, and pepper to the pan, and increase temperature to medium-high. Cook, stirring occasionally, until livers are just turning light pink in the center, 3 to 4 minutes. If you’re unsure how cooked the livers are, cut one in half to check.. Transfer to a food processor. Add heavy cream, remaining 4 tablespoons butter, and nutmeg, and blend until very smooth, adding a little more cream if necessary to reach a good spreading consistency.. Transfer to a bowl, cover, and refrigerate until firm, at least 3 hours or overnight.. Serve in ramekins or small jars, and garnish as desired.

name: Caramel Apple Cheesecake Dip
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'whole', 'name': 'graham crackers'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'no-bake cheesecake filling mix'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'caramel dip'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'whipped cream or whipped topping'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'roasted salted peanuts, coarsely chopped'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'sliced apples'}
steps: Place graham cracker crumbs in the bottom of a pie plate or deep serving dish. Carefully spread cheesecake filling over graham cracker crumbs, taking care not to mix the crumbs into the filling.. Microwave caramel dip for 10 seconds to loosen it and spread dip evenly over cheesecake filling.. Spread whipped topping over caramel and sprinkle evenly with peanuts.  Freeze for 10 minutes before serving, or refrigerate until ready to serve with sliced apples, pretzels and cookies.

name: 10 Layer Dip
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'refried beans'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'guacamole'}, {'quantity': '16', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'packet', 'name': 'taco seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded lettuce'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'roma tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'jalapeno'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'pepper Jack cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'black olives'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped cilantro'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pickled jalapeno slices'}
steps: Spread beans into an even layer on the bottom of a deep casserole dish. Spread guacamole over beans in an even layer.. Stir together sour cream and taco seasoning until well blended. Spread sour cream mixture over guacamole layer.. Spread Cheddar cheese evenly over sour cream layer and top evenly with lettuce.. Combine tomatoes, onion, jalapeno, and salt in a medium bowl and spread mixture evenly over lettuce.. Top tomato mixture evenly with pepper Jack cheese. Next top evenly with olives, then cilantro, and finally, with pickled jalapenos, taking care to keep each layer separated. Serve immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve.. Serve with hearty corn chips or tortilla chips.

name: Nashville Hot Mozzarella Sticks
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) block', 'name': 'mozzarella cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs,'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'hot sauce'}, {'quantity': '1 1/3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'seasoned breadcrumbs'}, {'quantity': '2/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'panko breadcrumbs'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'vegetable oil for frying, or more as needed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'ranch dressing for dipping'}
steps: Cut mozzarella cheese into 8 “plank”-shaped pieces, about 1/2-inch thick.. Whisk flour in a shallow dish with 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper. In a second shallow dish, add beaten egg and whisk in hot sauce. In a third shallow dish, stir together breadcrumbs and 1 teaspoon paprika. Set a wire rack inside a rimmed baking sheet.. Coat each piece of cheese in flour and shake off excess. Coat evenly with egg mixture and then place in the breadcrumbs. Coat evenly with breadcrumbs.. Return cheese to the egg and back into breadcrumbs, lightly pressing to adhere breadcrumbs. Place breaded cheese on the prepared wire rack. Repeat breading process with remaining cheese pieces. Place in freezer for 30 minutes.. Meanwhile, pour oil into a deep saucepan to a depth of 3 inches, and heat oil to 365 to 375 degrees F (185 to 190 degrees C). Combine remaining salt, pepper, and paprika with garlic powder, cayenne, and brown sugar in a heatproof bowl; stir until well blended.. Working a few at a time, carefully lower cheese pieces into hot oil. Fry about 1 minute, turning occasionally, until golden brown and crisp. Drain on wire rack.. Carefully pour 1 1/4 cups hot oil into the bowl with cayenne mixture and stir until well combined. Coat each cheese stick lightly in seasoned oil and return to wire rack to allow excess to drip off.. Serve with ranch dressing for dipping.

name: Nicole's Jalapeno Cranberry Cream Cheese Dip
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cranberries'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup dried sweetened cranberries,', 'name': 'dried sweetened cranberries,'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'bunch', 'name': 'cilantro, chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'jalapenos'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'orange marmalade'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green onions'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'whipped cream cheese'}
steps: Place frozen cranberries, dried cranberries, half of chopped jalapenos, and cilantro in a food processor and pulse until finely chopped. Transfer cranberry mixture to a bowl.. Stir in marmalade and salt. Reserve 2 tablespoons green onions for topping and stir in remaining green onions.. Spread cream cheese onto a serving plate and top with cranberry mixture. Sprinkle with remaining jalapeno and reserved green onions.  Serve with crackers.

name: Million Dollar BLT Dip
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'roasted almonds'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'sharp Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'Roma tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'green onions'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'bacon bits,'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'lettuce'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'crackers for serving'}
steps: Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, almonds, cheese, and garlic powder in a bowl and stir well.. Reserve 2 tablespoons tomatoes for garnish and add remaining tomatoes into mayonnaise mixture, along with green onions and bacon.  Stir well and season to taste with salt and pepper.. Spread mixture into a serving dish and top with lettuce, reserved tomatoes, and more green onions and bacon. Refrigerate until ready to serve with crackers.

name: Doritos Sausage Balls
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'chorizo, casings removed'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'breakfast sausage, casings removed'}, {'quantity': '1 1/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'baking mix (such as Bisquick'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'finely ground nacho cheese-flavored chips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8-ounce) package', 'name': 'Mexican cheese blend'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'pickled jalapeno'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fresh cilantro'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'salsa'}
steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil or parchment paper sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.. Using a stand mixer with a paddle attachment, beat together sausages, Bisquick, Doritos, cheese, jalapeño, and cilantro with until well blended.. Using a small ice cream scoop, scoop and roll 1-inch balls, and place 1-inch apart on prepared baking sheet. Bake in preheated oven until cooked through, about 20 minutes.. While sausage balls bake, stir together sour cream and salsa. Serve sausage balls with sour cream-salsa dip.

name: Roscoe's Korean Fried Chicken
ingredients: {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'wingette or drummette', 'name': 'chicken wings'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': None, 'name': 'chicken legs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'ginger'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'potato starch'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cornstarch'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'wheat dextrin, (Such as EverCrisp'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'quart', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ginger'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'gochujang'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'white vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'toasted sesame seeds, or as needed for garnish (optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'peanuts , or as needed for garnish (optional)'}
steps: Place a wire rack inside a rimmed baking sheet. In a large bowl toss chicken wings, chicken legs, ginger, garlic, salt, pepper, and water together. Mix well.. In another bowl combine flour, potato starch, cornstarch, and EverCrisp in a large mixing bowl. Whisk ingredients until fully mixed. Season with salt and pepper.. Add 1 cup of flour mixture to the bowl with chicken. Mix into chicken and water to make a very thin batter.. Add chicken to the flour bowl and toss and press until completely dredged in mixture. Place on the prepared wire rack until ready to fry.. Heat oil in a deep fryer or large saucepan to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). Line a second rimmed baking sheet with paper towels, and place a clean wire rack on top.. Add chicken pieces to the hot oil about 5 pieces at a time so as not to drop the temperature of the oil. Fry for 6 minutes. Transfer chicken to the rack over the paper towel-lined baking sheet tray. Continue with remaining chicken pieces.. Increase oil temperature to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) until continuously boiling. Carefully add the first batch of cooked chicken and fry again until cooked through and crispy, about 5 minutes more. Transfer to a plate lined with paper towels to drain. Repeat with the second batch of chicken pieces.. Transfer chicken to a medium-sized serving bowl. Heat a small saucepan over medium-low heat. Add sesame oil, grated garlic, grated ginger, brown sugar, gochujang paste, vinegar, and 1/2 cup water. Cook and stir continuously until sugar has melted and sauce is smooth, about 5 minutes. Drizzle sauce over twice-fried chicken pieces, garnish with sesame seed and peanuts, and serve.

name: Caprese Garlic Bread
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 ounce) loaf', 'name': 'French bread'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'olive oil spray'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'salted butter'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'mozzarella cheese'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'tomatoes'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh basil'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'balsamic glaze'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C), and line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Cut bread in half lengthwise, lightly spray with olive oil, and place on the baking sheet, cut side up.. In a small bowl, combine butter and garlic; spread evenly on the bread halves, and top with mozzarella slices.. Bake in the preheated oven until cheese is melted, and bread edges are starting to brown, 8 to 11 minutes.. Remove from the oven, place tomato slices on top of the cheese, season with salt and pepper, and sprinkle with basil. Drizzle with balsamic glaze, cut into slices, and serve.

name: Fig, Prosciutto, and Goat Cheese Pinwheels
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'sheet', 'name': 'puff pastry'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fig preserves, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'prosciutto'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'goat cheese, at room temperature'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'fresh rosemary'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped walnuts'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg, beaten'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}
steps: Thaw puff pastry according to package directions. Unfold puff pastry sheet on a lightly floured work surface.. Spread pastry with fig preserves, leaving bare about 1 inch from the edge of the left short side.. Cover preserves with prosciutto slices, and use a knife or offset spatula to cover prosciutto with goat cheese. Sprinkle evenly with chopped fresh rosemary and chopped walnuts.. Beginning on the right short side, gently roll up puff pastry and its contents into a log shape. With dampened fingertips, moisten the left, uncovered edge of puff pastry and then continue to roll, ending with seam side down.. Wrap filled puff pastry log loosely in parchment paper and refrigerate for about 20 minutes.. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C) and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.. Slice chilled puff pastry log crossways into 3/4-inch pinwheels and place on the prepared pan.. Add about 1 tablespoon water to egg in a small bowl, and beat with a fork until well blended. Brush pinwheels with egg wash and sprinkle lightly with coarsely ground pink salt.. Bake in the center of the preheated oven until lightly browned, 15 to 18 minutes. Remove to cool on a wire rack for 5 minutes. Serve warm, or at room temperature. Garnish with additional fresh rosemary, if desired.

name: Beetlejuice-Inspired Shrimp Cocktail
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'shrimp'}, {'quantity': '1/2 cup plus 2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'garlic clove'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'poblano pepper, seeded'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grapeseed or canola oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '6 to 8', 'unit': None, 'name': 'basil leaves'}
steps: Place shrimp, shells on, in a large bowl. Add 1 tablespoon olive oil, salt, and pepper and toss.. Heat a cast iron skillet over medium heat until hot; add 1 tablespoon olive oil to the skillet.. Cook shrimp in the skillet, without crowding, for 3 to 4 minutes on each side. You may have to work in batches. Remove shrimp from skillet and allow to cool.. Combine egg, poblano pepper, garlic clove, lime juice, and basil in a food processor and blend until smooth. With processor running, slowly add 1/2 cup grapeseed oil and process until mixture is smooth and thick.. Transfer mixture to a bowl and very slowly, a drop or two at a time, whisk in remaining 1/2 cup olive oil by hand. Season with salt and pepper.

name: Sardine Dip
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cans', 'name': 'sardines in oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'cream cheese,'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green onions, chopped, green and white parts'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'spicy brown mustard'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'fish sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'seafood seasoning, (such as Old Bay® Original)'}
steps: Combine sardines, cream cheese, mayonnaise, green onions, mustard, fish sauce, and Old Bay seasoning in a large mixing bowl. Mix well by hand or with an electric mixer.

name: Watermelon Carpaccio
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'watermelon'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': None, 'name': 'basil leaves,'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'pepitas or a nut of your choice'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'feta'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lemon balsamic glaze'}
steps: Wash the outside of the watermelon with a fruit and veggie cleaner. Cut watermelon in half. With flesh of watermelon facing down, cut thin slices.. With a paring knife, remove the rind from the watermelon. Cut watermelon slices into triangles.. Arrange on a platter and top with feta and pepitas. Drizzle with lemon flavored balsamic glaze and serve.

name: Spiced Pecans
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg white, lightly beaten'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'pecan halves'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cloves'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil.. Beat egg white and water together in a large bowl; add pecans and stir to coat.. Mix sugar, cinnamon, salt, cloves, and nutmeg in a small bowl; sprinkle over moistened nuts. Spread nuts on the prepared pan.. Bake in the preheated oven, stirring once or twice, until toasted and fragrant, about 30 minutes.

name: Easy Garlic Knots
ingredients: {'quantity': '10', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'pizza dough'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'extra-virgin olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'minced garlic'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fresh parsley'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crushed red pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease a large baking sheet.. Roll out dough on a lightly floured surface to a 10x16-inch rectangle. Cut dough lengthwise into 12 strips. Halve strips to make 24 (8-inch-long) strips. Tie each strip in a knot. Arrange on prepared baking sheet.. Bake in the preheated oven until golden brown, 10 to 15 minutes. Transfer knots to a large bowl. Drizzle with oil. Sprinkle with garlic, Parmesan, parsley, crushed red pepper, and salt. Toss gently to coat.

name: Salad Kit Spring Rolls with Sesame Dipping Sauce
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'mirin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 to 13 ounce)', 'name': 'Asian-style salad kit with sesame dressing'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': None, 'name': 'rice papers'}, {'quantity': '16', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'cooked shrimp'}, {'quantity': '2/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cucumber'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh cilantro'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'sliced green onions, for garnish'}
steps: For dipping sauce, stir together mirin, soy sauce, and sesame dressing from salad kit in a small bowl.. Line a tray with damp paper towels. Put a clean, slightly damp kitchen towel on a work surface. Fill a shallow dish with cold water.. Working one at a time, soak a rice paper in cold water just until it starts to soften, about 30 seconds, and transfer to prepared work surface. Arrange 4 shrimp halves, about 1/3 cup salad kit greens, a few pieces of cucumber, and 1 tablespoon cilantro on bottom third of rice paper, leaving a 1-inch border. Bring up bottom edge of rice paper to cover filling. Fold in sides and roll up tightly.. Transfer roll to prepared tray; cover with additional damp paper towels to prevent drying. Repeat soaking, filling, and rolling with remaining rice papers, shrimp, greens, cucumber, and cilantro, leaving space between rolls to prevent sticking. Garnish dipping sauce with green onions and serve with spring rolls.

name: Baked Turkey Curry Empanadas
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '14', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'ice water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'yellow onion'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'curry powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground turkey'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg yolk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'Greek-style yogurt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'mango chutney'}
steps: Stir together flour and salt in a large bowl. Cut butter into flour mixture with a pastry blender or fork until pea-size pieces form. Mix in ice water, 1 to 2 tablespoons at a time, just until dough comes together. (Dough should hold together when gently squeezed.) Divide dough into 2 portions; wrap each in plastic wrap. Chill at least 1 hour or up to 2 days.. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook onion, stirring frequently, until tender, about 4 minutes. Stir in 1 tablespoon curry powder and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute.. Add ground turkey, soy sauce, and remaining 3 tablespoons curry powder. Cook, stirring and breaking up lumps, until turkey is browned, about 8 minutes. Remove from heat; let filling cool completely.. Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C). Line a large baking sheet with parchment paper. Working with one portion of dough at a time, remove plastic and roll out dough on a lightly floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness. Use a 3 1/2-inch round cutter to cut out circles, rerolling scraps as needed. Repeat with remaining dough until you have 24 circles.. Holding a dough circle in your palm, add 1 heaping tablespoon filling. Fold dough over filling and pinch (or use a fork) to seal edges. Repeat with remaining dough circles and filling. Arrange empanadas about 1/2- inch apart on the prepared baking sheet.. Beat together egg yolk and water in a small bowl; brush onto empanadas. Prick each empanada with a fork to vent. Bake until golden brown and crisp, 15 to 18 minutes. Let cool slightly.. Meanwhile, for creamy mango sauce, stir mayonnaise, yogurt, and mango chutney together; serve with empanadas.

steps: Preheat the grill to medium-high heat. Lightly coat the grate with cooking spray.. Combine melted butter, Parmesan cheese, and garlic powder in a medium bowl. Coat chicken cubes with mixture.. Thread chicken cubes onto each skewer. Grill until chicken is no longer pink at the center and juices run clear, turning skewers every few minutes, 15 to 20 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted near the center should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).

steps: Preheat the air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C) according to manufacturer’s instructions.. Place cubed potatoes in a large bowl. Add olive oil and toss to coat.
